James de Villiers, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Western Cape police are investigating the origin of a hand grenade that exploded in a Cape Town home on Monday, seriously injuring six youths."Circumstances surrounding an explosion [on Monday] at about 18:30 in Goud Street, Vanguard Estate, [near] Manenberg, whereby six young males aged between 15 and 20 years old were seriously injured are under investigation," spokesperson Captain Frederick van Wyk said.The six youths were rushed to separate hospitals. A case of unlawful possession of explosives was opened.Five teenagers were injured, two of them critically, Western Cape EMS spokesperson Robert Daniels said.They had been taken to Groote Schuur Hospital and a private hospital.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.